<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>General</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Run Speed 3<br>
Regen 3<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Archtype</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Natural Durability 3<br>
Finishing Blow 1<br>
Combat Agility 1<br>
Combat Stability 1<br>
Regen 1<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Class</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Area Taunt<br>
Physical Enhancement<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>PoP Advanced</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Planar Durability 3<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>PoP Abilities</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Ingenuity 1<br>
Stalwart Endurance 1<br>
<br>
I have chosen my points either cos they seemed fun or they were essential for hit points and a little mitigation in there so far.  But now I am stuck on what I should choose next.  Do I want the Marshall title, i mean its only 14 points away, I could use 9 in ambidex and 3 in flurry.  But this means ill have to max combat fury, a further 12 points.  But a good fun skill and good for dps too.  Or another option, I spend 20 points maxing CA and CS for good old fashioned tanking, and then go onto PoP mitigation too but no class title.  Or I can max all the pop skills available to me at the moment im not sure!<br>
<br>
